<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Coat Weight" class="currentChild" href="Coat_Weight">Coat Weight</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A measure of the amount of <a title="Coating" href="Coating">coating</a> added to a <a title="Base Stock" href="Base_Stock">base stock</a> of paper in the manufacturing of <a title="Coated Paper" href="Coated_Paper">coated paper</a>s. The coat weight of a particular paper is determined by such factors as the desired <a title="Basis Weight" href="Basis_Weight">basis weight</a> and paper <a title="Grade" href="Grade">grade</a>. As the basis weight is decreased, the coat weight must be decreased to provide uniformity and the desired degree of <a title="Caliper" href="Caliper">caliper</a>, strength, <a title="Opacity" href="Opacity">opacity</a>, and other desired properties. There are a variety of different methods utilized to apply coatings to paper. (See <a title="Coating" href="Coating">Coating</a>.) Coat weight is usually measured as pounds of coating on the surface of a 25 x 38-inch ream of paper. 
</p>
